        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a 63-year-old Czech woman with a medium build and slightly pale complexion, presenting to the oncology clinic in Prague for follow-up after a recent diagnosis of malignant neoplasm of the breast. She first noticed a firm, painless breast lump in her left breast approximately three months ago [SNOMED:C50.9], followed by mild nipple discharge that prompted her to seek medical attention [SNOMED:C50.9]. On examination, there is visible swelling and mild irritation of the overlying skin of the left breast [SNOMED:C50.9].\n\n{patientName} is a retired schoolteacher who spent over 30 years teaching literature at a secondary school in Brno. She enjoys tending to her garden, reading classical Czech literature, and participating in a local book club. She lives alone in a modest apartment since her husband passed away four years ago, but maintains close contact with her adult daughter who lives nearby and accompanies her to most medical appointments.\n\nShe describes her overall lifestyle as moderately active — she walks daily and cycles occasionally in the warmer months. She has never smoked and drinks wine only on special occasions. Her diet is typical Central European, rich in dairy and meat. She is generally in good spirits despite her diagnosis, though she admits to experiencing significant anxiety about the treatment process and what lies ahead."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:19a96015-1ebf-41d4-bc50-007cd3d65186",
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Communication",
        "status": "completed",
        "text": {
          "status": "generated",
          "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">patient-history</div>"
        },
        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has a past medical history of well-controlled type 2 diabetes mellitus (on oral agents), mild osteoporosis diagnosed at age 58, and hypertension managed with lifestyle modification. She reached menopause at age 51 and has never received hormone replacement therapy. She has no prior history of breast cancer or other malignancies. She was hospitalized once briefly in 2018 for a urinary tract infection that required intravenous antibiotics. There is a significant family history of breast cancer in her mother (deceased at age 67). {patientName} underwent a screening mammogram two years ago which showed no abnormality, making the current presentation particularly alarming. She has no prior chemotherapy or radiation therapy. She does not use tobacco or recreational drugs. Her body mass index is approximately 27 kg/m². She reports occasional mild joint pain consistent with osteoarthritis. She takes no regular immunosuppressive or hormonal medications."
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
